Project Overview

This project demonstrates how to deploy a Python Flask web application on an AWS EC2 instance (Amazon Linux) using EC2 Instance Connect.
The application provides a simple web UI to accept user input and store it in a file on the EC2 server.
========================================================
KEY TERMINOLOGY : 
1) PIP : pip is a tool to download Python libraries.
Think like this üëá
Python = mobile phone üì±
pip = Play Store / App Store
Flask = an app you download using pip
So without pip, you cannot download Flask.

Flask is a Python web framework.
In simple words:
Flask helps Python talk to a browser.
Without Flask:
Python runs only in terminal
No website
No web UI
With Flask:
You can open Python app in Chrome / Safari
You can create forms
You can take user input from browser

What Flask does for you
Flask allows Python to:
create a website
listen on a port (like 5000)
receive browser requests
send responses back

=========================================================
Tech Stack: 

Cloud Provider: AWS
Service: EC2
OS: Amazon Linux
Language: Python 3
Framework: Flask
Access Method: EC2 Instance Connect (Browser-based)
Port Used: 5000

