===========================================================

‚öôÔ∏è Setup Steps (Step-by-Step)

1) Connect to ec2
AWS Console ‚Üí EC2 ‚Üí Instance ‚Üí Connect ‚Üí EC2 Instance Connect

2) Update system :
Command -- sudo yum update -y

3) install python and pip :
Command -- sudo yum install python3 python3-pip -y
Verify -- python3 --version
          pip3 --version
4)INSTALL FLASK :
 Command -- pip3 install flask

5) CREATE DIRECTORY :
COMMAND -- mkdir web_ui
           cd web_ui
6) CREATE FLASK APP FILE AND OUTPUT FILE :
COMMAND -- vi app.py
          then enter your code 
          touch outputfile.txt
7) RUN FLASK :
COMMAND -- python3 app.py

8)OPEN IN BROWER :
ADDRESS -- http://<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>:5000

============================================================

üîê Security Group Configuration
   Custom TCP | Port 5000 | Source 0.0.0.0/0
   # rembember this at the time of creating instance and if not attach it afterword
=============================================================

COMMON ERROR :

‚ùå Error 1: pip3: command not found

Reason: pip not installed
Fix:

sudo yum install python3-pip -y

‚ùå Error 2: Browser keeps loading / ERR_CONNECTION_TIMED_OUT

Reason: Port not allowed in Security Group
Fix:

Open port 5000 in Security Group

Use correct URL:

http://<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>:5000

‚ùå Error 3: ERR_CONNECTION_REFUSED

Reason: Flask running on wrong port or not accessible
Fix:

Check Flask output

Ensure same port is used in browser and Security Group

‚ùå Error 4: Permission denied (when using port 80)

Reason: Ports below 1024 require root privileges
Fix:

sudo python3 app.py

‚ùå Error 5: curl: Failed to connect to 127.0.0.1

Reason: Flask app not running
Fix:

python3 app.py

‚ùå Error 6: App running but public IP not opening

Reason: Confusion between IPs
Clarification:

127.0.0.1 ‚Üí Local only

Private IP ‚Üí AWS internal

Public IPv4 ‚Üí Browser access

====================================================

Key Learnings

Flask must bind to 0.0.0.0 for external access

Security Groups act as firewalls

EC2 Instance Connect does NOT require SSH keys

Port mismatch is the most common issue in EC2 deployments


